('2543', '1', 'Bring milk to a simmer over medium heat in a medium, heavy saucepan.'),
('2543', '2', 'Add fish. cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
('2543', '3', 'Drain well.'),
('2543', '4', 'Combine fish, 1/4 cup panko, and next 8 ingredients (through 1 garlic clove). stir in 1 tablespoon juice. Divide fish mixture into 8 equal portions, shaping each into a 1/2-inch-thick patty. Dredge patties in remaining 1/4 cup panko, pressing to coat.'),
('2543', '5', 'Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('2543', '6', 'Add 4 patties to pan, and cook for 4 minutes on each side or until golden.'),
('2543', '7', 'Remove from pan, and drain on paper towels. Repeat procedure with remaining olive oil and patties.'),
('2543', '8', 'Drizzle with remaining 1 tablespoon juice.'),
('2543', '9', 'To prepare sauce, combine canola mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.'),
('2543', '10', 'Serve sauce with cakes.'),
('2544', '1', 'For the fish stock: Coat a large, tall pot lightly with olive oil.'),
('2544', '2', 'Add the onions, celery, and fennel tops and bring the pot to a high heat. Season the veggies lightly with salt. Cook the veggies until they are soft and very aromatic, 7 to 8 minutes.'),
('2544', '3', 'Add the garlic and cook for 1 to 2 minutes more.'),
('2544', '4', 'Add the fish bones and shrimp shells, stir to combine, and cook for 3 to 4 minutes.'),
('2544', '5', 'Add the anise-flavored liqueur and let it reduce by half.'),
('2544', '6', 'Add water to the pot until it covers the fish bones by 2 inches and season lightly with salt. Toss in the bay leaves and thyme bundle. Bring the pot to a boil, reduce to a simmer, and simmer for 30 minutes. Strain the liquid and reserve.'),
('2544', '7', 'For the fish: Coat a straight-sided saute pan with olive oil.'),
('2544', '8', 'Add the onions and fennel, season with salt, and cook over medium heat until the veggies start to soften, 3 to 4 minutes.'),
('2544', '9', 'Add the garlic and cook for 1 to 2 minutes.'),
('2544', '10', 'Add the anise-flavored liqueur and white wine and reduce by half.'),
('2544', '11', 'Add the reserved fish stock and season with salt. Bring to a boil, reduce to a simmer, and simmer the broth for 12 to 15 minutes. Taste to make sure it is delicious.'),
('2544', '12', 'Meanwhile, coat a second saute pan with olive oil. Bring the pan to a high heat. Pat the cod dry with paper towels and season with salt.'),
('2544', '13', 'Add the cod to the screaming hot pan and cook the fish until it is golden and crisp on both sides and 3/4 of the way cook through.'),
('2544', '14', 'Remove the fish from the pan and reserve. Do the same with the shrimp and reserve.'),
('2544', '15', 'Add the potato rounds to the pan, season with salt, and brown on both sides.'),
('2544', '16', 'Remove the potatoes from the pan and reserve with the cod and shrimp.'),
('2544', '17', 'When the fish broth is ready, add the cod, shrimp, potatoes, and zucchini. Turn off the heat and cover, letting the fish gently cook through, 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('2544', '18', 'To serve, remove the cod and shrimp from the pan. Scoop the veggies out of the broth and divide them between 4 serving bowls. Lay a piece of cod on top of each of the veggies and arrange 2 shrimp next to the cod. Ladle the fish broth over each piece of cod.'),
('2544', '19', 'Drizzle with big fat finishing oil and top with fennel fronds.'),
('2545', '1', 'In a large soup pot, saute the fennel and onion in a few tablespoons of your F.O.C. (Id recommend bacon renderings!) until soft.'),
('2545', '2', 'Add the creamer & stock.'),
('2545', '3', 'Let it come to a simmer.'),
('2545', '4', 'Add the fish pieces and let them poach until theyre cooked through, about 10 minutes. Stir in the lemon juice.'),
('2545', '5', 'Serve topped with crumbled bacon & chives.'),
('2547', '1', 'Heat large skillet to medium heat. Melt butter and saut onions, garlic, and red pepper until soft, 7-10 minutes.'),
('2547', '2', 'Remove from heat and set aside. In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and cooked vegetables together. Form palm-sized patties by pressing mixture in between hands.'),
('2547', '3', 'Place on greased cookie sheet.'),
('2547', '4', 'Bake at 350 for 20 minutes.'),
('2547', '5', 'Serve with sweet rice, black beans and/or avocado tomato salsa.Mexican Sweet Rice'),
('2549', '1', 'Soak the baccala in cold water for 24 hours to re-hydrate, changing the water 3 times to remove the salt.'),
('2549', '2', 'Drain and rinse under cold water and put into a large pot.'),
('2549', '3', 'Add the milk and enough water to cover by 1-inch. Cook uncovered over medium heat for 45 minutes.'),
('2549', '4', 'Drain and set aside to cool. When fish is cool enough to handle, shred the fish into a bowl, taking care to get all the bones out.'),
('2549', '5', 'Add onion, parsley, and tomatoes. In a separate bowl, whisk together olive oil, vinegar, lime juice, and salt and pepper.'),
('2549', '6', 'Add the dressing to the cod salad, toss and serve.'),
('2550', '1', 'Coat a jelly-roll pan with cooking spray. Coat bottom of pan evenly with canola oil. Set aside.'),
('2550', '2', 'Rinse fish fillets in running water. pat dry on paper towels. Sprinkle salt evenly on each side of fillets.'),
('2550', '3', 'Cut fish into 1- x 2-inch strips. set aside.'),
('2550', '4', 'Beat eggs, egg whites, and milk in a pieplate or shallow dish with a fork until well blended.'),
('2550', '5', 'Place Lemony Breading'),
('2550', '6', 'Mix in a large zip-top plastic bag. Dip fish strips into egg mixture. add a few at a time to breading mix in bag. Shake to coat.'),
('2550', '7', 'Place breaded fish in prepared jelly-roll pan. repeat with remaining fish strips.'),
('2550', '8', 'Bake at 400 for 15 to 20 minutes or until breaded fillets are golden brown.'),
('2550', '9', 'Serve immediately.'),
('2552', '1', 'Topping:70g hazelnuts and boiled chestnuts70g yellow sugar60g butter at room temperature'),
('2552', '2', 'Grab a bowl and grate the zest from 1 orange. Also squeeze out the juice.'),
('2552', '3', 'Place all the dough ingredients in bread machine in the order suggested by your manufacturer. Select "Dough" cycle.Chop coarsely the filling hazelnuts and boiled chestnuts.When the cycle ends, add chopped hazelnuts and chestnuts and coconut, then select "Dough" cycle again. This will make the dough extremely fluffy.'),
('2553', '1', 'Heat 1 tsp. oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.'),
('2553', '2', 'Add onion and cook until softened, about 3 minutes.'),
('2553', '3', 'Add fennel seeds, rosemary, tomatoes, chickpeas, wine, and broth and cook, covered, until boiling.'),
('2553', '4', 'Meanwhile, cut fish into 1-in. chunks and add to boiling broth. Reduce heat and simmer until fish is cooked through and pulls apart when poked with a fork, about 3 minutes.'),
('2553', '5', 'Remove rosemary sprig, season with salt and pepper, and spoon into bowls.'),
('2553', '6', 'Drizzle each serving with oil, sprinkle with parsley, and serve with warm, crusty bread.'),
('2554', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('2554', '2', 'Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.'),
('2554', '3', 'Place bread crumbs in a shallow dish. Pile parsley, garlic, lemon zest, and a little coarse salt on the cutting board. Finely chop the lemon-garlic mixture, then combine with plain bread crumbs.'),
('2554', '4', 'Brush the top of each fillet with olive oil and dip in to the bread crumb herb mixture.'),
('2554', '5', 'Brush a little bit of olive oil in the bottom of a baking pan then place fillet in the pan, crust side up. Roast fillets in oven until firm to the touch, about 12 to 15 minutes.'),
('2556', '1', 'Mise en'),
('2557', '1', 'Heat the oil in a skillet over medium heat.'),
('2557', '2', 'Place onion in the skillet. Reduce heat to low, and cook, stirring often, 15 minutes, or until soft and brown.'),
('2557', '3', 'Mix the garlic paste and ginger paste into the skillet. Cook 1 minute.'),
('2557', '4', 'Mix in cumin, coriander, cardamom, turmeric, and salt. Stir in the jalapeno, cilantro, lemon juice, and tomatoes with juice, scraping up any brown bits from the bottom of the skillet. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer 20 minutes. If you like, the sauce may be set aside for a few hours at this point to allow the flavors to blend.'),
('2557', '5', 'Return the sauce to a boil, and place cod in the skillet. Reduce heat to low, and cook 15 minutes, or until fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('2558', '1', 'Special equipment: 3 disposable pie tins'),
('2558', '2', 'Pour 2-inches of vegetable oil into a large skillet.'),
('2558', '3', 'Place skillet over large burner and heat oil over medium high heat. To check if the oil is hot enough, drop in 1-inch cube of white bread. The bread should brown in a 40 count.'),
('2558', '4', 'Cut cod into 4 servings, 6 to 8-ounce portions and season with salt and pepper.'),
('2558', '5', 'Place a couple of scoops of flour in a pie tin.'),
('2558', '6', 'Combine egg and water in second tin. Season plain bread crumbs and mustard and cayenne in the third tin. Coat fish in flour, then egg, and then bread crumbs. Gently set coated fish into hot oil and fry 5 minutes on each side until medium golden brown in color.'),
('2558', '7', 'When the fish is evenly golden all over, remove and drain on brown paper sacks.'),
('2558', '8', 'Suggested: 3 disposable pie tins .'),
('2560', '1', 'In a small bowl, mix 1 Tbs. of the ginger, the soy sauce, vinegar, 2 Tbs. water, and about a quarter of the scallions. Set the dipping sauce aside.    Rinse the cod and pat dry it with paper towels. Season both sides lightly with salt and pepper.'),
('2560', '2', 'Put the flour in a shallow bowl.'),
('2560', '3', 'Put the egg whites in a medium bowl and whisk until a thick foam forms on the surface. To the egg whites, add the garlic, chiles, and the remaining ginger and scallions and mix well.'),
('2560', '4', 'Heat the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Dredge each piece of cod on both sides first in the flour and then in the egg whites, using your hands to press the scallions and chiles onto the fish.'),
('2560', '5', 'Transfer to a plate.    When the oil is hot (it will bubble if you put a scallion ring in it), add the cod, spacing the pieces evenly (you may have to cook them in two batches), and raise the heat to medium high. Turn the fish over after 3 minutes. Reduce the heat to medium and cook until the fish is firm to the touch and flakes apart easily when pierced with a fork, about another 4 minutes.'),
('2560', '6', 'Serve immediately with the dipping sauce and the lime wedges on the side.    Serving Suggestions'),
('2560', '7', 'Serve with white rice and spinach sauted with garlic, or with soba noodles in broth.'),
('2561', '1', 'Rinse fish and pat dry. Peel onions and cut lengthwise into quarters, keeping root ends intact.'),
('2561', '2', 'Brush both sides of the fish fillets and the onion quarters with oil. Sprinkle evenly with salt and pepper. Wrap stack of tortillas in foil.'),
('2561', '3', 'Set tortillas and onions on an oiled barbecue grill over medium-hot coals or medium-high heat on a gas grill (you can hold your hand at grill level only 3 to 4 seconds). close lid on gas grill. Cook tortillas until hot, turning 2 or 3 times, 10 to 15 minutes total.'),
('2561', '4', 'Place warm tortillas in a napkin-lined basket. Cook onions, turning once, until cooked through and lightly charred, 10 to 15 minutes total.'),
('2561', '5', 'Grill the fish, turning once, until barely opaque in center of thickest part (cut to test), 6 to 8 minutes total.'),
('2561', '6', 'Arrange fish, onions, and lime wedges on a platter or divide among plates. Offer relish and salsa to add to taste.'),
('2562', '1', 'Place fish in large bowl.'),
('2562', '2', 'Add enough water to completely cover fish.'),
('2562', '3', 'Let stand at room temperature 8 hours, changing the water at least every 2 hours to remove excess salt.  Rinse fish. place in large skillet.'),
('2562', '4', 'Add enough water to completely cover fish. bring to boil on medium-high heat.  Reduce heat to medium-low. simmer 5 min or until fish is tender.  Rinse fish.  Shred with fork. place in medium bowl.'),
('2562', '5', 'Add flour, water, onions, eggs, parsley, baking powder and pepper. mix well.'),
('2562', '6', 'Heat oil in large deep skillet to 375F.  Carefully add level tablespoonfuls of the fish mixture, in batches, to skillet.  Cook until golden brown, turning occasionally.'),
('2562', '7', 'Drain on paper towels.'),
('2567', '1', 'Mash the potato in a large bowl.'),
('2567', '2', 'In a small skillet, cook the bacon and scallions until the meat is crisp, about 5 minutes.'),
('2567', '3', 'Add the bacon and scallions to the bowl.'),
('2567', '4', 'Mix in the cod, peas (if using), egg, salt, and pepper.'),
('2567', '5', 'Cover and chill for 30 minutes.'),
('2567', '6', 'Put the cornflake or Chex crumbs in a shallow bowl. Form the cod mixture into 6 three-inch round patties. Press all sides of them into the crumbs.'),
('2567', '7', 'Heat the oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('2567', '8', 'Fry the cakes for 1 to 2 minutes a side.'),
('2567', '9', 'Serve them on the buns, with tartar sauce or mayonnaise.'),
('2568', '1', 'Preheat oven to 400F.'),
('2568', '2', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('2568', '3', 'Add onions and cook, stirring often, until just starting to soften, 5 to 7 minutes.'),
('2568', '4', 'Add wine, increase heat to high and cook, stirring often, until the wine is slightly reduced, 2 to 4 minutes.'),
('2568', '5', 'Place cod on the onions and sprinkle with thyme, salt and pepper. Cover the pan tightly with foil. transfer to the oven and bake for 12 minutes.Toss bread with the remaining 1 tablespoon oil, paprika and garlic powder in a medium bowl.'),
('2568', '6', 'Spread the bread mixture over the fish and top with cheese.'),
('2568', '7', 'Bake, uncovered, until the fish is opaque in the center, about 10 minutes more.'),
('2569', '1', 'Season fish with salt and pepper. Dip fish in flour, then egg and dredge in panko mixture, pressing firmly to coat.'),
('2569', '2', 'Place on a large lightly greased baking sheet.'),
('2569', '3', 'Bake at 400F 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes evenly when tested with a fork.'),
('2569', '4', 'Serve with mayonnaise mixture'),
('2571', '1', 'Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).'),
('2571', '2', 'Into a food processor, place the roasted red peppers*, horseradish sauce, and Worcestershire sauce. Pulse until smooth.'),
('2571', '3', 'Pour 1/4 cup roasted red pepper sauce into a 13x9-inch baking dish, and spread to coat the bottom.'),
('2571', '4', 'Place fish in baking dish, and season with garlic pepper. Cover fish with remaining sauce. Sprinkle each fillet with crushed Cajun snack mix.'),
('2571', '5', 'Bake in preheated oven until the crumbs start to brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.'),
('2573', '1', 'Fish Sticks: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.'),
('2573', '2', 'Brush canola oil on a rimmed baking sheet and set aside.Crack egg(s) into a shallow dish and beat lightly (start with one egg and crack another if you run out). In a separate shallow dish combine flour, seasoned salt, pepper, and paprika. In one more shallow dish combine panko and bread crumbs.'),
('2573', '3', 'Cut fish into sticks about 3-4 inches long and 1/2-1 inch tall.Working with a few pieces of fish at at time, dredge first in flour and then shake off excess. Then dip each piece in the beaten egg, and finally the bread crumb mixture. Make sure all sides are well coated with bread crumbs and then place fish on the baking sheet.When all pieces are on baking sheet, place in oven and cook for about 10 minutes. Cool for a few minutes and then serve with tartar sauce for dipping.'),
('2574', '1', 'Combine the garlic, ginger, scallions, honey, soy sauce, grapeseed oil and vinegar in a mixing bowl. Marinate the fish fillets in this mixture for at least 2 hours, preferably overnight, refrigerated.'),
('2574', '2', 'Transfer the cod and marinade to a shallow pan and slowly poach the fish over low heat until it is fork tender, 10 to 20 minutes.'),
('2574', '3', 'Slice the baguette into 18 pieces and lay out on a baking sheet.'),
('2574', '4', 'Brush with olive oil.'),
('2574', '5', 'Preheat oven to 450 degrees F.'),
('2574', '6', 'Remove fish to a utility platter and flake.'),
('2574', '7', 'Transfer flaked cod to a strainer set over a bowl to drain excess moisture. Discard this excess liquid and put the flaked cod into the bowl.'),
('2574', '8', 'In another small bowl, combine mayonnaise, scallions and relish to make a tartar sauce. Gently fold this tartar sauce into the flaked fish to help bind it.'),
('2574', '9', 'Put the cod on the crouton and place in oven until the fish has a golden brown hue.'),
('2574', '10', 'Remove from oven and garnish with each appetizer with 1/8 teaspoon caviar and a small amount of parsley before serving.'),
('2577', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('2577', '2', 'Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.'),
('2577', '3', 'Rinse fish and squeeze lemon juice over it. Season the fish with a little salt and reserve.'),
('2577', '4', 'Heat a large oven proof pan over medium heat.'),
('2577', '5', 'Add extra-virgin olive oil, fennel and onion and season with salt.'),
('2577', '6', 'Saute fennel and onions 7 to 8 minutes then add white wine and reduce a minute, then add broth.'),
('2577', '7', 'Add tomatoes and season with salt and pepper. Set fish into pan and spoon juices over the cod.'),
('2577', '8', 'Add a few sprigs dill to the broth and set the pan into the hot oven to cook. Cook 12 minutes, until fish is opaque. To serve, arrange cod on plate, top with vegetables and chopped fresh dill.'),
('2580', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('2580', '2', 'Wash off all the salt from the salted cod fish in cold water, and then soak as follows: Soak for 1 hour in hot water, and then drain and replace with a new batch of hot water for another hour. The fish will be soaked for a total of 2 hours.'),
('2580', '3', 'Heat the oil in a medium skillet over medium heat and then add the chopped garlic and cook for 30 seconds.'),
('2580', '4', 'Add the sprig of thyme and cook for 30 seconds.'),
('2580', '5', 'Add the onions, scallions, bell peppers, and Scotch bonnet pepper and cook for 5 minutes. Stir the entire mix as needed.'),
('2580', '6', 'Add the prepared codfish to the skillet and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring as needed.'),
('2580', '7', 'Add the ackee to the skillet and simmer for another 2 minutes. Stir in the black pepper and turn off the stove.'),
('2580', '8', 'Garnish the cooked meal with the paprika.'),
('2582', '1', 'Rinse the fish in cold water, then soak for 48 hours in 4 changes of cold water.'),
('2582', '2', 'In a large bowl, combine the semolina flour, the all-purpose flour, the baking powder, baking soda, salt, 2 tablespoons olive oil and enough water so that a loose batter is formed.'),
('2582', '3', 'In a tall-sided pot or deep fryer, heat the olive oil to 375 degrees F.'),
('2582', '4', 'Dip each fillet in the batter, allowing the excess to drip off, then dip in the bread crumbs to coat. When the oil is at temperature, gently drop the fillets in the oil and cook until golden brown and crisp, about 5 minutes.'),
('2582', '5', 'While the fish cooks, in a medium-sized bowl, combine the parsley, onion and tomatoes and toss with 2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil, lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste.'),
('2582', '6', 'Remove the fish from the oil, season with salt and pepper, briefly drain on a plate lined with paper towels, and serve with 1/4 of the salad mounded atop each portion.'),
('2584', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('2584', '2', 'Put the eggs, beer, mustard, chili powder, 1 tablespoon salt and sugar in a medium bowl and mix until smooth.'),
('2584', '3', 'Add the flour and continue mixing until it is a little thinner than pancake batter.'),
('2584', '4', 'In a deep-fryer or heavy-bottomed pot, heat enough vegetable oil to come halfway up the sides of the pot, to 375 degrees F. Dredge the fish pieces in flour and then into the batter and fry until golden brown.'),
